U.S. Stocks Extend Losses on Concern Over Japan Nuclear Plants After Quake

-- B y   M i c h a e l   R e g a n
-- 
2011-03-16T15:07:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/u-s-stocks-extend-losses-on-concern-over-japan-nuclear-plants-after-quake.html
U.S. stocks extended losses as
concern grew that  Japan ’s nuclear crisis will worsen.  The Standard & Poor’s 500  Index sank 1.1 percent to
1,267.81 at 11:05 a.m. in  New York . The  Dow Jones Industrial
Average  sank 144.11 points, or 1.2 percent, to 11,711.31.  Dow Jones reported that the European Union’s energy
commissioner said the situation at damaged nuclear reactors
north of  Tokyo  is out of control and possible catastrophic
events may occur in hours.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  